org.jsapar.compose.bean

Class RecordingBeanEventListener<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jsapar.compose.bean.RecordingBeanEventListener<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<T>, EventListener, BeanEventListener<T>

    public class RecordingBeanEventListener<T>
extends Object
implements BeanEventListener<T>, Iterable<T>
    Saves all beans that was composed into a list that can be retrieved by calling getBeans() when done composing. The Generic type T should be set to a common base class of all the expected beans. Use Object as base class if there is no common base class for all beans. A ClassCastException will be thrown if the bean created could not be converted into the class defined by T. Created by stejon0 on 2016-10-15.

        public void beanComposedEvent(BeanEvent<T> event)
